Airports of Thailand Pcl, Thailandâ€™s
biggest airport operator, said full-year profit almost doubled
on foreign-exchange and investment gains.  Net income was 1.42 billion baht ($46.9 million), or 0.99
baht per share, in the fiscal year ended September, from 717.3
million baht, or 0.50 baht, a year earlier, the company said in
a statement today.  Airports of Thailand reported a foreign-exchange gain of
309.4 million baht in the period, compared with a loss of 1.85
billion baht a year earlier. The company also had a 185.5
million baht gain on the sale of investments, according to its
